From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Local Build Fix <local@meta-beta>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] openat2: use const open_how pointer

Recent glibc headers declare openat2() as:

  int openat2(int, const char *, const struct open_how *, size_t)

Pseudo's wrapper input used a non-const open_how pointer, which generated
conflicting prototypes and breaks pseudo-native compilation on newer hosts.

Align the wrapper declaration with glibc by making the parameter const.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Local Build Fix <local@meta-beta>
---
 ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in b/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in
index de95cf1..5af8478 100644
--- a/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in
+++ b/ports/linux/openat2/wrapfuncs.in
@@ -1 +1 @@
-int openat2(int dirfd, const char *path, struct open_how *how, size_t size);
+int openat2(int dirfd, const char *path, const struct open_how *how, size_t size);
-- 
2.34.1
